column3: 2100 Spaulding Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90016
column8: Beautifully renovated traditional house on a corner lot offering superb curb appeal and style. Combining 1940s character with modern updates & flair, the inviting porch leads to an open living room lined with windows around the fireplace providing an abundance of natural light. The seamless flow of the living and dining room is highlighted by the newly laid floors, light fixtures and paint, creating an ideal place to entertain. The remodeled kitchen features new appliances, counters and backsplash while preserving the original cabinets and detail. Surplus storage beyond the spacious bedrooms, the highly functional floor plan includes a service porch with a powder room and laundry area. The detached garage with its pitched ceiling could be converted to an ADU (zoned LARD2) and/or serve as a home office/studio. Endless gardening possibilities in the front, side and back yards. Culver City Arts District adjacent, across from Ballona Creek bike path, this lovely neighborhood provides close access to the Westside, LAX and Downtown LA.

column3: 1902 N Screenland Dr, Burbank, CA 91505, USA
column8: You've been waiting to see this one and finally the wait is over!  Introducing 1902 N Screenland Drive.  This charming single story home is a must see to believe opportunity in one of the premier locations within the Valley.  When you enter the property you are treated to hard wood floors and recessed lighting that bring in pleasant contemporary feel.  The soft tones of the interior paint match the home's decor perfectly throughout.  As you head toward the kitchen passing through a lovely dinning room area where you could add a breakfast nook to enjoy your morning coffee.  The bedrooms are delicately placed off to the right side as you enter the property.  The backyard has the potential for an entertainers paradise as it boast room enough to do a pool, guest house, even a half sized basketball court.  It even has four fruit bearing trees outback.  You are close to the Hollywood Bowl, all of the TV studios, Center Staging Music Rehearsal Studios, Universal City Walk, and minutes away from the Burbank Airport.  The possibilities are endless, the time to act on this one is now.

column3: 22328 De Grasse  Drive, Calabasas, CA 91302
column8: This stunning single-story home in Mulwood boasts an impressive layout featuring 4 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms. Upon entering the home, you are welcomed by soaring vaulted ceilings that create a spacious and inviting atmosphere, a cozy fireplace, and generous living room areas. The expansive kitchen offers multiple options for dining room and breakfast nook spaces. The primary bedroom is roomy with several closets and an en-suite bathroom equipped with a shower and separate tub. The three additional bedrooms are located down the hall, providing privacy for a home office or gym, and each has built-in organization in the closets. The backyard serves as a true oasis, complete with a pool and spa, BBQ area, and lush greenery. One of the key features of this home is its solar panels, which were installed in 2020. Conveniently located within close proximity to high-end shopping, dining, and entertainment options, this home is situated in the coveted Las Virgenes School District.

column3: 1023 Via Colinas, Westlake Village, CA 91362
column8: Absolutely gorgeous townhouse in the best location at the top of Hidden Canyon. This 3 bedroom, 2.5 bath, townhouse is ready to move right in. Remodeled kitchen, hardwood floors, beautiful atrium and outdoor patio let the light and nature right inside. Two car attached garage with laundry hook up. All bedrooms are upstairs. Living room features high ceilings and fireplace. Well maintained HOA features security, pool, spa, and playground.

column3: 7539 Bobbyboyar Ave, West Hills, CA 91304, USA
column8: This wonderful property offers a great balance between open floor plan living while still defining space. Featuring a formal living room with vaulted high ceilings that flows into a spacious family room with gorgeous French doors, gas fireplace, stunning view of the backyard, and a desk nook perfect for a home office. The versatile formal dining room could also be used as a sitting area or reading room. A well equipped chef’s kitchen features granite countertops, center island, an abundance of cabinet space, and updated appliances. A bay window above the farmhouse sink overlooks the backyard and brings in plenty of natural light. Upstairs, the primary suite features double French doors, remodeled en-suite bath with built-in vanity, double sinks an a tiled step-in shower. The magical backyard is perfect for entertaining or relaxing. With direct access to the kitchen through the sliding glass doors, the beautiful patio area with wooden pergola provides shade and creates a wonderful indoor-outdoor living area for dining and entertaining guests. The pool and spa with surrounding palm trees and green hedges make this backyard a true private oasis. An attached two-car garage provides convenient access to the home and additional storage. There is even more storage in the separate laundry room. Zoned for award winning El Camino Real Charter High School. Close to parks, hiking trails, dining and shopping at Westfield Topanga, The Village and much more! Other recent updates include: dual pane windows, new roof, upgraded pool equipment, carpet, primary bathroom remodel, solar panels, and attic insulation.

3/1 DH: Gladys did not remove the solar panels yet, and is still seeking approval and funding from her insurance. We tried to connect and left couple of VM advising that with this delays and since the pricing changed, we will not take on this project.

1/10 JB SW Gladys-said Tesla is emailing her something to sign on her phone-probably start February
Gladys had USAA, her insurance company, visit about new damage above the fireplace. They were upset no work has been done with the money they gave her, said the $1k for Tesla was included with the money they are giving her, and we should pay Tesla. 

I reminded her we didn’t take the $1k to get started so she has it to pay them, that if we pay we assume the liability and we can’t do that, and we have the check sitting uncashed that we can return to her so she can figure it out elsewhere.

Gladys needs to call Tesla January 5th to get a better appointment 877 731-7652 or 877 798-3752
12/28 JB SW Gladys-she was told the panels can't be removed until February 2024
12/19 Doron: Contract sent to Joey as Gladys does not have email according to Joey. Joey is going to collect signature on his device and provide Gladys hard copy. During the signature Joey will make sure Gladys understand that $800 permit fees are collected separatly (not part of SOW). He will also collect $1,000 for first milestone, and get the date for the solar panel removal (homeowner responsibility) so that we can schedule the roofing provider (start of work).

12/18 Joey sent revised bid $20,800 

12/13 Doron: Ram confirmed roofer cost is $14,000, and Solar would be the minimum $1500 (according to the agent they have 6 panels). Updated PDF share with Ram for final approval.

12/12 Doron: Talking to Ram cost for removal and re-install of solar is $180 per panel with minimum of $1500. Ram also mentioned that he need to re-quote the complete roof as it is too low. Joey to get number of panels so that we can add to the quote. Ram to provide updated roof cost.

column3: 10794 Wilkins ave suite 404 Los angeles ca 90024
column8: Welcome to this newly remodeled fabulous corner penthouse unit located in prime Westwood, close to UCLA, Westwood village, and future Metro Purple line. Enter into this magical open living /dining area boasting floor-to-ceiling windows, allowing floods of light and a peek-a-boo view of Wilshire hi-rises and city lights. This beautiful designer renovated 2 bedrooms/2.5 baths with loft unit offers comfortable living at its best. The primary suite includes a spacious walk-in closet and a master bathroom with a double sink, Jacuzzi tub, and separate stall shower. The kitchen features all stainless steel appliances and a breakfast nook with direct access to the open dining room. A dramatic black iron staircase then leads you to the loft and rooftop deck, offering breathtaking views of Hollywood Hills, adding more charm to this gorgeous, turn-key penthouse! The building amenities include a pool, spa, sauna, and banquet room. Parking is tandem with wall unit storage in the security, gated parking. Rental restrictions may apply.

column3: 4900 La Crescenta Blvd, La Crescenta, CA 91214
column8: A house with a wide and an open open floor plan, this is an immaculate single-story La Crescenta home with plenty of space for a family to grow. With four larger-than-usual bedrooms, three magnificently designed bathrooms the layout gives the right balance of a modern floorpan and everyone their privacy. The interior is crafted with neutral whites, gleaming tiles, and hardwood-style floors. Recessed lighting highlights the living room while elegant chandeliers glow above the foyer and dining area, and a bonus skylight ushers in natural light. Plenty of cabinetry and countertop space, stainless steel appliances, and a wine cooler highlight the all-white kitchen, while a modern fireplace features in the dining area, making for a cozy eating experience. The generous master showcases a walk-in closet and chic ensuite with a soaking tub, glass-enclosed shower, and a double-sink vanity. To compliment the beauty of the interior of the home, it also offers a backyard with a play area, pool, waterfall, and patio. Numerous buyers have actively looked for homes in this neighborhood because of its close proximity to La Crescenta's schools which are top rated in the state: Monte Vista Elementary, a National Blue Ribbon school, Rosemont Middle School and Crescenta Valley High School. The oversized lot offers an abundance of outdoor space with a wonderfully landscaped backyard, a heated pool, Sonos speaker system and a patio creating the ideal space for entertaining guests. Additional must-have features include a laundry room, an owned solar panel, two central A/C and heating for bedrooms and common areas, outdoor CCTV with DVR, a power outlet for any EVs(240V), and an attached two-car garage. With thoughtful upgrades for modern living, you’ll get to experience fine 21st-century living in an impeccable abode. Come get a glimpse before the opportunity passes you by!

column3: 6401 Nohl Ranch Rd suite 78, Anaheim, CA 92807
column8: This handsomely upgraded single family home will not last on the market! It is part of the coveted gated community of Nohl Villas which offers a pool, spa and ample guest parking. Walk-through the double door entry and see how it leads to a bright and spacious floor plan. The downstairs offers an elegant formal living room and dining room. The remodeled kitchen includes new kitchen appliances such as a refrigerator, dishwasher, stove and microwave unit, and granite counters. All bathrooms have been remodeled and upgraded. The primary suite features a vaulted wood beam ceiling, a remodeled bath with dual sinks, a walk-in closet and a balcony. Additional upgrades include: HVAC system and heater, dual pane windows and sliding doors, shutters, a tankless water heater, garage opener and paint, recessed lighting and attic insulation. It is ideally located near shopping, dining, parks, trails, Oak Canyon Nature Center, the AH Golf Club and the AH Saddle Club.

column3: 8275 Fernadel Avenue, Pico Rivera, CA, USA
column8: Home features a family friendly layout. Spacious Living room with fireplace, open to the dining area, kitchen was recently updated with quartz counter tops, ample cabinets with plenty of storage. One car garage with plenty of parking space in the driveway. Newer energy efficient windows and central heating and AC. Very private enclosed backyard for family gatherings. Property is located in the Pico Rivera/Downey borderline. Garage was converted to an room extra w/o permits.

column3: 14159 Weddington St, Van Nuys, CA 91401
column8: Hidden behind it's own xeriscaped garden oasis, this private and charming Sherman Oaks home exudes easy living. Come into the foyer with all new tile floors and find a charming living room ready for entertaining. A cozy gas-burning fireplace centers the spacious living room that also features character pieces like built-in shelving and original wood floors. Move the party to the extraordinary dining room ready to seat 12 comfortably. While dinner is prepared, the large kitchen continues the character with a built-in rotisserie (not operable but neat!) and gas stainless steel appliances. A den with a built-in workspace leads out to the low-maintenance yard and peaceful patio.  All the bathrooms are BRAND NEW, with new toilets, tilework, tub/shower surrounds, vanities, etc. 3rd bedroom makes a great office or flex space. The entire home has been freshly painted both inside and out, as well as new tile flooring throughout. Packed to the gills with green lifestyle choices, including xeriscaped native yards that are eco-friendly, to a tankless water heater and solar panels (leased, but paid for 20 years in advance, the lifetime of the contract). Dual paned windows also conserve energy. Copper plumbing. Cleanouts are all cleared. New can lighting throughout. Roof was replaced within 10 years.  Newer HVAC and newer thermostat, both of which have recently been serviced.  With nearby restaurants, shopping, and easy freeway access, this Sherman Oaks home is centrally located and ready for you to arrive, move in ready.

column8: Enter this wonderfully secluded, hill side home ideally located south of the boulevard. Private courtyard entry leads you gracefully into this light and bright 4 bedroom, 4 bathroom exquisite home. Large formal living room with vaulted ceilings and sliding glass door makes indoor-outdoor living a breeze. Huge kitchen with eat-in area, double oven and gas range overlooking the pool ensures you~ll always be where the action is. The master bedroom suite offers a pool view and ample space for a king sized bed plus sitting area. It also comes well equipped with his/hers bathrooms, enormous walk in closet and built ins. Sit outside and enjoy the city lights view by the pool/spa area which is kept private with mature landscaping. Other property features include: den, security system, dual zone A/C, 3 car garage. Please read private remarks for showing instructions.
